SUMMARY:Spring fling-Annual Wash DC Cherry Blossom Ride RSVP  required
DESCRIPTION:Lancaster Bicycle Club (LBC) Meetup\nThe Spring fling weekend 
 of the Lancaster Bicycle Club\, and Wilmington Rails for Trails will be he
 ld on the weekend of March 27-29\, 2026\, Washington DC Cherry Blossom rid
 e.\nWhere we have stayed previous years is now permanently closed.\nSo thi
 s year we will be staying at:\n\nThe Double Tree-Hilton\n300 Army Navy Dri
 ve\nArlington\, VA 703-416-4100\nWe have a special rate per room/ two quee
 n beds/ per night of $179\nThis rate is held until March 6th…\nTo regist
 er click on the following:\n[https://www.hilton.com/en/attend-my-event/dca
 aedt-500-eef3e4a2-105a-4fd5-a39e-7d51d68f2aea](https://www.hilton.com/en/a
 ttend-my-event/dcaaedt-500-eef3e4a2-105a-4fd5-a39e-7d51d68f2aea)\n\n**Tent
 ative schedule:**\nFriday afternoon arrive and check in. 4pm We will meet 
 in the parking lot and ride the trails Four mile run\, Mount Vernon\, etc.
  …back by dark.\nSaturday ride to see Cherry Blossoms. Once again this y
 ear\, we have Mary\, who lives in DC will ride with us\, as our guide for 
 the day.\nSunday after checking out\, some of us will choose to stop\, on 
 the way home\, and ride the Capital Crescent Trail between Bethesda and Ge
 orgetown.\nThe trails we are riding are crushed gravel. Hybrid bicycles ar
 e recommended\,but road bikes will do… so RSVP required on Meet Up and c
 ontrol/ click the link above.\n\nRichard Conner 717-572-8480
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/lancaster-bicycle-club/events/3131907
 32/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260203T173218Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260203T173218Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
